<font color="#FF0000">AN ANSWER TO SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Fri Apr 25 14:48:05 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
What needs to be talked about is how thin a line exists between the racism of today and the racism of Reinhard Heydrich and Adolf Eichmann. Just this past weekend here in Hawaii, we have had our own little &quot;Kristallnacht&quot;,(the one day that every synagogue in Germany was destroyed).  Seven cemetaries, spread over the entire Island of Oahu, were extremely vandalized by a mainland hate group. It was very well organized and well orchestrated. The cemetaries included Punchbowl national Cemetary of the Pacific, the final resting place for veterans and their families and where my own daughter is buried. Her(our) grave plaque was one of many that were disecrated and possibly destroyed.<br><br>
And before any anti-semetic, racist, facist son of bitch accuse me of being a Jew, you would be honoring me by doing so, but defaming their race. I will accept &quot;Jew luvin'&quot; if you think that will hurt me. I am as pearly white as you can get, born protestant, though I KNOW there is no god. (and I don't want any born-agains saving my &quot;soul&quot; and don't want to hear from bible thumpers, either, because, it'll cost ya! That I promise!!)<br><br>
It is unfortunate that the likes of Dr. Barry Spatz and others and not been a target of racism, nor seen the effects of such in it's extreme form. Like having to dig up a mass grave of an entire Cambodian village, and a five year old girl lays at your feet. How about the good doc just taking the place of one of those towns in Bosnia laid seige by their counterparts and then having the entire town massacred because you happened to be Muslim. How about just the subtle or not so subtle day to day racism that many folks have to endure, which can be as painful as having thin strips of skin cut by a dull knife.<br><br>
Now, I am sure some simple minded individuals would like to speak of reverse-discrimination and the like, but before you get stupid with that argument, let me inform you that the assholes who RAPED my daughters grave, left messages accusing Hawaii of the very same thing. It is a very convenient thing to do when you hate colors other than white. I have lived here all my life and it is total BULLSHIT. Its called fucken &quot;justification&quot;. Trying to justify your own garbage that is within youself. Doesn't work with this guy.<br><br>
You had hope that I did not put you on that racist list. I don't have to do any such thing. You, dear, Doc, have made your own bed.<br><br>
For those who thought little of my daughter, I would like to truely see how much guts you have. My address is 626, Pualani Way, Pukalani.  And I know you have no brains to figure out what Island I live, so let me help you. Its Maui. Look at it this way. We all gotta die for a cause! Xin Loi!
